  "text": "There is a mathematical theory for the self-organization of solutions of the 2D Navier-Stokes equations developed by van Groesen in [CITATION_1] . To the best of our knowledge, the mathematical CFD community seems to be only little aware of this theory. Thus, for the interested reader, this theory will be sketched in this section, thereby extending it to the boundary conditions present in the Kelvin-Helmholtz instability problem. The most important conclusions from this theory for this problem are summarized in Remark 3.6 and 3.7.",
